This paper is about optimization methods in deep learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper evaluates a variety of optimizers on standard datasets and architectures, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses neural networks, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper proposes a practical and universal quantitative measure for optimizer tunability, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
